Affordable Housing Navigator – Programming Outline

 Affordable Housing Navigator – Programming Outline

 Phase 1 – Project Setup
 1. Create Java project.
 2. Create main class: AffordableHousingNavigator.
 3. Import libraries:
    - Scanner
    - ArrayList
    - HashMap

 Phase 2 – Data Structures
 4. Create shared data structures:
    ArrayList<String> HOUSING_PROGRAMS
    HashMap<String, ArrayList<String>> RESOURCES_BY_ZIP
    ArrayList<String> FAVORITES

 Phase 3 – Initialization
 5. Write initPrograms() method.
 6. Write initResources() method.

 Phase 4 – Menu System
 7. Create printMainMenu() method.
 8. In main(), create while loop to keep program running.
 9. Use switch statement to call feature methods.

 Phase 5 – Features

 Feature 1: Rent Affordability Calculator
 - Ask for monthly income
 - Calculate recommended rent (income * 0.30)

 Feature 2: Browse Housing Programs
 - Display list of programs
 - Allow user to select and view details

 Feature 3: Waitlist Estimator
 - Input applicants ahead
 - Input placements per month
 - Compute wait time

 Feature 4: Tenant Rights Information
 - Display submenu of rights topics

 Feature 5: Find Local Housing Resources
 - Ask for ZIP code
 - Look up resources in HashMap
 - Display list
 - Option to save favorite

 Feature 6: Favorites Manager
 - Display saved resources
 - Remove or clear favorites

